# Hospital Management System (HMS) Implementation Plan

Build a production-ready, feature-rich Hospital Management System (HMS) with a separate Next.js + Tailwind CSS frontend and a Node.js + Express + Prisma + Socket.io backend. The system supports four distinct roles: Super Admin, Doctor, Nurse, and Patient, with secure RBAC and real-time updates.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **Database Credentials**: By default, the backend will be configured to run with a local PostgreSQL instance or SQLite for ease of local development. For production, Supabase connection details will need to be provided in the backend `.env` file.
> - **Cloudinary Config**: File uploads for medical reports and user profiles require Cloudinary credentials (`CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME`, `CLOUDINARY_API_KEY`, `CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET`). If not supplied initially, a local fallback storage service will save files to disk so development can proceed seamlessly.
> - **PowerShell Script Policy**: Since script execution is disabled on the current Windows machine, all Node/NPM commands will be executed via `npm.cmd` or `npx.cmd`.

## Proposed Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    User([User Browser]) -->|Next.js App / Tailwind / Shadcn| FE[Frontend Server]
    FE -->|HTTP API Requests| BE[Express.js Backend]
    FE -->|WebSocket Events| WS[Socket.io Real-time Server]
    BE -->|Prisma Client| DB[(PostgreSQL / Supabase)]
